data.answer: Yes, the diffraction pattern changes indicating the structure of UNLPF-16 may be affected by the reaction.

data.question: What is the proposed mechanism for the [3+2] cycloaddition of aziridines and alkenes?
data.answer: The proposed mechanism involves the coordination of the Lewis acid to the β-C of the alkyne with respect to the nitrogen tether.

Can the product molecules of the [3+2] cycloaddition of aziridines and alkenes freely diffuse out of the MOF UNLPF-14-MnIII?
data.answer: Yes, for products 9a-h, the dimensions allow for efficient diffusion out of the MOF, but not for product 9i.

data.answer: Yes, the heterogeneity test indicates the reaction is mostly heterogeneous.

data.question: What is the proposed mechanism for the [4+2] hetero-Diels-Alder reaction?
data.answer: The proposed mechanism involves the coordination of the aldehyde to the cationic metal center of the MOF, activating the substrate for the cycloaddition.
